The paper discusses challenges related to measuring software quality from the user's perspective, which is a key aspect of software engineering (cs.SE). It also mentions the importance of e-learning applications and mobile service-based applications, which fall under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybersecurity (cs.CY) respectively. The proposed framework uses sentiment analysis techniques, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
